<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1971,2036]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,152,216]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,283,1971,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Tergites 
<number box="[399,444,1971,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
with yellow erect hairs and tergites 
<number box="[894,940,1971,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
with black erect hairs, tergites 
<number box="[1328,1373,1971,1997]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
with yellowish recumbent scales on anterior half, and tergites 
<number box="[842,888,2010,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="57" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
with yellowish recumbent scales posteriorly; sternite 
<number box="[244,258,152,178]" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" value="4.0">4</number>
with white scales. Gonostylus acute and narrowed from base to tip in lateral view; epiphallus with a nearly round tip in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
