<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,337,963,989]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet derives from the Latin “ 
<taxonomicName box="[856,940,964,990]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusa">obtusa</taxonomicName>
”; referring to obtuse tip of the distiphallus in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,1040,1066]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[686,933,1041,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[686,811,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">V. fasciata</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated from the latter by tergites 
<number box="[250,295,1080,1106]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
with yellowish recumbent scales on anterior half, but scales on tergite 
<number box="[1179,1194,1080,1106]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="3.0">3</number>
less. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1300,1428,1080,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[1300,1428,1080,1105]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">V. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tergites 
<number box="[247,262,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[322,337,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="3.0">3</number>
have yellowish recumbent scales antero-laterally, tergite 
<number box="[1033,1048,1118,1144]" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" value="4.0">4</number>
has yellowish recumbent scales anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
